    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nFollowing example:\n```cython\ncdef float main():\n     cdef list a = ['this', 'are', 'strings']\n     cdef list[float] b = a\n     return b[0] * b[2]\n```\nShould yield compile time error.\n\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nCython should not allow assigning general type to more specific one. The good is that currently cython does all checks during accessing item so the error is reported to the user during runtime:\n\n```python\n>>> import a\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"<python-input-0>\", line 1, in <module>\n    import a\n  File \"a.pyx\", line 23, in init a\n    main()\n  File \"a.pyx\", line 19, in a.main\n    return b[0] * b[2]\nTypeError: must be real number, not str\n```\n\nDisabling this assignment is simple - False needs to be return here:\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/af063fd6d5edf031f0b47eaab5e1856afc5c1122/Cython/Compiler/PyrexTypes.py#L5033-L5034\n\nThe hardest part is to check assignment of constants to variables:\n```\ncdef list[float] a = [1.0, 2.0, 3.0]\n```\nWhere the constant should be checked if adher the variable type (`list[float]`)\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\nDo nothing is also possible but I think compile time error is better than wait till code is executed for giving an error...\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "You probably meant the last line to be\n\n```\nreturn b[0] * b[2]\n```\n\nInstead of `a[0] * a[2]`.\n\nI don't think this is a compile time error though. That forces everything to be fully typed which seems very restrictive.",
